1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
What if I told you the sun has a bubble around it?

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,400
This bubble is called the heliosphere, and it protects us from harmful cosmic rays.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,800
The solar wind creates this protective shield, extending far beyond Pluto.

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,000
But what happens when cosmic rays breach it?

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,600
They can affect our technology and even our climate.

6
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:22,800
Isn’t that wild?

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,200
Curious to learn more about space?

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,200
Follow for more science facts!
